    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-threshold factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted given corroborating analytical sensitivity studies and the inherent conservatism of the ASTM F1717 compression-bending protocol. Validation metric satisfied for all three QoIs. Overall credibility is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
